Post.title: Git
Post.author: zayfen
Post._content:
![git flow](https://res.cloudinary.com/zayfen/image/upload/v1568171685/img/l8yeyxvtfw6kplg1ci67.png)

### git log
```sh
git log --graph --pretty=format:'%Cred%h%Creset -%C(yellow)%d%Creset %s %Cgreen(%cr)%Creset' --abbrev-commit --date=relative
```

### commit
```sh
### add 
git add <file(s)>

### add all changes to commiter queue
git add .

### commit
git show <commit-id>
git diff <commit-id>^!
##### e.g. git show d34ff657f5   git diff d34ff657f5^!
``` 

### 
```sh
git commit -m "commit message"

### also can combine git add & git commit in one command
git commit -m "commit message" -a
```

### 
```sh
### origin originbranch_name 
git push origin <branch-name>
```

## 
### 
```bash
### from existed repo 
git clone <repo-url>

### create a new local repo
git init [<local-directory>]
```


## 
### 
```sh
### 
git branch

### 
git branch -va

### 
git remote show <repo-name> ## git remote show origin
```

### 
```sh
### 
git checkout <new-branch-name>

### 
git checkout -b <new-branch-name>

### 
git checkout -b <local-branch-name> <repo-name>/<remote-branch-name>
#### e.g.: git checkout -b test origin/test

###  (--tranck )
git branch <local-branch-name> <repo-name>/<remote-branch-name> [--track]
#### e.g.: git branch test origin/test
```

### 
```bash
## 
### remote-name:  origin local-branch-name:  remote-branch-name: 
 git push <remote-name> <local-branch-name>:<remote-branch-name>
 
 ## 
 ### 
 git push -u <remote-name> <branch-name>
 #### or
 git branch --set-upstream-to=<remote-name>/<remote-branch> <local-branch>
 
```

### 
```bash
### 
git pull

### 
git remote update

###  v1.0
git checkout .
git pull

### v2.0
git fetch --all
git reset --hard origin/master
git pull

```

## Tag

### tag
```bash
git tag -a <tag-name> -m <tag-message>
```

### tag
```bash
### tag
git tag -d <tag-name>

### tag
git push --delete <repo-name> <tag-name>
or 
git push <repo-name> :refs/tags/<tag-name>

### e.g.: git push --delete origin tag-r0
### e.g.: git push origin :refs/tags/tag-r0
```

### tag
```bash
### tag
git tag

### tag
git tag -l <tag-name>

### tag
git show <tag-name>
```

### tag
```sh
## push single tag
git push <remote-name> <tag-name>

## push all tags (not recommended)
git push --tags
```


### 
```sh

git reset --hard # removes staged and working directory changes

## !! be very careful with these !!
## you may end up deleting what you don't want to
## read comments and manual.
git clean -f -d # remove untracked
git clean -f -x -d # CAUTION: as above but removes ignored files like config.
git clean -fxd :/ # CAUTION: as above, but cleans untracked and ignored files through the entire repo (without :/, the operation affects only the current directory)

```


### githttps
```bash

$ git config credential.helper store
$ git push https://github.com/owner/repo.git

Username for 'https://github.com': <USERNAME>
Password for 'https://USERNAME@github.com': <PASSWORD>

## push

## 

git config --global credential.helper 'cache --timeout 7200'

## 7200push

```

3 dogcatpigcat
dog =>  bitmap[1], bitmap[2], bitmap[3], 1dog

pig =>  bitmap[8], bitmap[9], bitmap[10]1 pig
hashbitmap
,birdhashbitmap1, bitmaphash

# 4. 

bitmaphash function

 bitmaphash function 

 KhashM bitsbitmap N, bitmapKhash
$$p_1=\frac{1}{M}$$~~~~


$$p_2=1-\frac{1}{M}$$

$$K$$
$$p_3=\left(1-\frac{1}{M}\right)^K$$

$$N$$N
$$p_4=\left(1-\frac{1}{M}\right)^{KN}$$


$$p_5=1-\left(1-\frac{1}{M}\right)^{KN}$$

Khash
$$p_6=\left(1-\left(1-\frac{1}{M}\right)^{KN}\right)^K$$

1$$p_6$$
 $$1-\frac{1}{m}\approx\ell^{-\frac{1}{m}}$$$$p_6$$$$\ell^{-\frac{KN}{M}}$$
$$p_6\approx\left(1-\ell^{-\frac{KN}{M}}\right)^K$$

$$K$$$$\frac{M}{N}\ln2$$ 
$$p_6\approx\left(1-\ell^{-\frac{\left(\frac{M}{N}\ln2\right)N}{M}}\right)^{\frac{M}{N}\ln2}$$
$$\ln{p_6}\approx{\frac{M}{N}\ln2}\times\ln\left(1-\ell^{-\frac{\left(\frac{M}{N}\ln2\right)N}{M}}\right)$$
$$\ln{p_6}\approx{\frac{M}{N}\ln2}\times\ln\left(1-\ell^{-\ln2}\right)$$
$$\ln{p_6}\approx{\frac{M}{N}\ln2}\times\ln\left(1-\frac{1}{\ell^{\ln2}}\right)$$
$$\ln{p_6}\approx\frac{M}{N}\ln2\times\ln\frac{1}{2}$$
$$\ln{p_6}\approx\frac{M}{N}\ln2\times{\left(-\ln2\right)}$$
$$\ln{p_6}\approx{-\frac{M}{N}{\left(\ln2\right)}^2}$$


$$M=-\frac{\ln{p_6}\times{N}}{{\left(\ln2\right)}^2}$$

  0.001,   10000  $$M$$  

    Math.log(0.001)*10000 / Math.pow(Math.log(2), 2) * -1 // output: 143775.87566051158

 K

    143776 / 10000 * Math.log(2) // output: 9.965... 10hash
